104
功能語法學 Syntax
http://ocw.nctu.edu.tw/course_detail.php?bgid=5&gid=0&nid=104
功能語法學 Syntax



	課程首頁

	

	本課程是由交通大學外國語文學系提供。

	

	This course is designed to give a general survey of current syntactic theories, with a special emphasis on functional approaches to grammar. It aims to explore the differences between &lsquo;formal&rsquo; and &lsquo;functional&rsquo; paradigms for syntactic analysis, with a thorough discussion of their 1) theoretical premises, 2) research concerns, 3) data collection 4) analytical methodology, and 5) explanatory principles. The first half of the class will focus on form-function associations as manifested in the English grammar. The second half will then introduce a variety of functional explanatory mechanisms with illustrations from a wide range of languages. The ultimate goal of this class is to familiarize students with contemporary syntactic theories that take grammar as coding devices for coherent communication.

	

	&ldquo;Syntax codes what people do the most&rdquo; &ndash; T. Givon.

--
功能語法學 Syntax    最後更新：2016/03/01  11:39 AM


177
語法與構詞 Syntax and Morphology
http://ocw.nctu.edu.tw/course_detail.php?bgid=5&gid=0&nid=177
語法與構詞 Syntax and Morphology



	課程首頁

	

	本課程是由交通大學外國語文學系提供。

	

	Language is a coding system. The formal devices used to code information are most relevant to syntax and morphology. This class is designed to explore the central roles played by syntax and morphology in human languages and to introduce the form-function association as realized in the so-called &lsquo;grammatical rules.&rsquo; Class lectures will focus on the English grammar and problems in Mandarin will be discussed as group project topics.

--
語法與構詞 Syntax and Morphology    最後更新：2016/03/01  11:38 AM


